<item>
            <title>[LU-10803] req_buffers_max and req_history_max setting problems</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10803</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We hit &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9372&quot; title=&quot;OOM happens on OSS during Lustre recovery for more than 5000 clients&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9372&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9372&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; OOM problems, and after applying&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9372&quot; title=&quot;OOM happens on OSS during Lustre recovery for more than 5000 clients&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9372&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9372&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ptlrpc: allow to limit number of service&apos;s rqbds&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; we found two problems:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160; &#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; 1)Since 0 is a reserved value for @srv_nrqbds_max which&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; means unlimited value, procfs write interface should support&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; this value, otherwise, there is no way to change default behavior&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; back.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; 2)the check in ptlrpc_lprocfs_req_history_max_seq_write() was broken&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; after this patch, the following check will always succeed if @srv_nrqbds_max&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; is kept as default value 0:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&#160; &#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160; val &amp;gt; svc-&amp;gt;srv_nrqbds_max/2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
